Success Nwogu, Abuja The Chairman of DAAR Communications Plc, Mr Raymond Dokpesi Jnr, has tested positive for coronavirus. The African Independent Television, a subsidiary of DAAR Communications Plc, reported on Monday that he made his status known in a short message to members of the AIT staff in Abuja. His message read, “I got a call this morning confirming the result is COVID-19 positive. I am leaving now to the Gwagwalada Isolation Centre for treatment and hope to be back in two weeks. Many of you may have interacted with me during our various meetings and I would advise you to get tested as soon as possible.” Copyright PUNCH.
